A 24-year-old man has died while another sustained
serious injuries in a road accident near Riat trading center in Ndhiwa, Homa
Bay County, on Thursday evening. The deceased, identified as Moses Ojwang,
died after his motorbike was hit by a tractor belonging to Sukari Industry Limited. According to South Kanyikela Location Chief Moses
Odhiambo Ongong'a, the driver of the tractor was trying to negotiate a corner
near when he lost control and hit the motorbike. Mr. Ongong'a said Ojwang together with his pillion
passsener, who remains unidentified, were rushed to a private hospital at Riat
center where Ojwang succumbed to injuries while undergoing treatment. The administrator said the survivor has been
referred to Ndhiwa sub-county hospital where he's admitted in a stable
condition. He added that the driver of the tractor abandoned
it after the accident and fled.  The body of the deceased has since been taken
to Manyataa Kobodo mortuary.